00:17:10.900 --> 00:17:13.579
who actually loves them and care for them,

00:17:13.579 --> 00:17:16.460
it changes their viewpoint towards themselves.

00:17:16.460 --> 00:17:19.180
And that also helps them to come in truth.

00:17:19.180 --> 00:17:24.539
Well, given the need and the response that you're getting,

00:17:24.539 --> 00:17:28.660
can you get help from other places like brothers or publishers

00:17:28.660 --> 00:17:30.019
from other countries?

00:17:30.019 --> 00:17:30.980
Absolutely.

00:17:30.980 --> 00:17:34.380
In fact, every year we organize special campaigns

00:17:34.380 --> 00:17:37.539
to try to cover some of our unworked territory.

00:17:37.539 --> 00:17:39.299
And we have friends come from other countries

00:17:39.299 --> 00:17:41.059
who support these campaigns.

00:17:41.059 --> 00:17:42.779
And how does that work out?

00:17:42.819 --> 00:17:45.940
Well, the friends who come really enjoy themselves.

00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:47.619
And they enjoy themselves so much

00:17:47.619 --> 00:17:51.500
that they often come back again for longer periods of time.

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:53.940
So you have need graders in India?

00:17:53.940 --> 00:17:55.019
We do.

00:17:55.019 --> 00:17:56.099
Could you use more?

00:17:56.099 --> 00:17:57.700
Oh, yes, please.

00:17:57.700 --> 00:18:01.500
And there is also a growing sign language field in India.

00:18:01.500 --> 00:18:05.220
The Deaf field is one of the fastest growing fields in India.

00:18:05.220 --> 00:18:08.619
For example, a few years ago, there was no Deaf congregations.

00:18:08.619 --> 00:18:11.140
But today we have 13 congregations

00:18:11.180 --> 00:18:13.900
and over 46 pregroups and groups.

00:18:13.900 --> 00:18:16.740
Wow, again, that's amazing response.

00:18:16.740 --> 00:18:19.980
Well, what kind of sign language do you use in India?

00:18:19.980 --> 00:18:22.740
Is it similar to American sign language?

00:18:22.740 --> 00:18:24.579
No, we have Indian sign language,

00:18:24.579 --> 00:18:27.500
which is very natural and very easy to learn.

00:18:27.500 --> 00:18:29.779
Actually, I can help you to learn some.

00:18:29.779 --> 00:18:30.740
You can try.

00:18:30.740 --> 00:18:31.740
Yeah, OK.

00:18:31.740 --> 00:18:34.420
So for sign for women, it's like this,

00:18:34.420 --> 00:18:36.980
because there were no strings.

00:18:36.980 --> 00:18:38.980
And for sign for men, it's like this,

00:18:38.980 --> 00:18:40.220
because they have moustaches.

00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:42.099
Not all, of course.

00:18:42.099 --> 00:18:46.380
And then if I just do act like I'm eating a fruit,

00:18:46.380 --> 00:18:48.059
so now I'm going to do a sign

00:18:48.059 --> 00:18:51.059
and let's see if you can understand, in guess.

00:18:51.059 --> 00:18:51.900
You give me a test.

00:18:51.900 --> 00:18:53.099
Yeah, it's from Bible.

00:18:53.099 --> 00:18:54.220
It's very easy.

00:18:54.220 --> 00:18:58.579
So if I do like which Bible correct me?

00:18:58.579 --> 00:18:59.539
Oh, very good.

00:18:59.539 --> 00:19:02.180
And if I do like that.

00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:02.779
Adam.

00:19:02.779 --> 00:19:04.420
Wow, very good.

00:19:04.420 --> 00:19:06.619
Have on my way to learning Indian sign language.

00:19:06.619 --> 00:19:08.779
Yes, yes.

00:19:08.819 --> 00:19:11.019
And Brother Stovall, the deaf people

00:19:11.019 --> 00:19:14.299
are really drawn to the attention they receive

00:19:14.299 --> 00:19:16.940
in the congregation, because unfortunately,

00:19:16.940 --> 00:19:19.579
in the Indian society, they are neglected.

00:19:19.579 --> 00:19:21.579
For example, there was a brother who

00:19:21.579 --> 00:19:25.819
was trying to contact a deaf man to arrange for a meeting.

00:19:25.819 --> 00:19:29.579
So the deaf man asked if he can bring a friend along.

00:19:29.579 --> 00:19:33.380
And when the brothers arrived at his village,

00:19:33.380 --> 00:19:36.299
they found the interested person, the deaf man.

00:19:36.299 --> 00:19:39.299
And not just one of his friends were with him,

00:19:39.299 --> 00:19:46.619
but 136 of his deaf friends had come along with him to listen.

00:19:46.619 --> 00:19:47.700
Incredible.

00:19:47.700 --> 00:19:52.660
How in the world could the brothers speak to 136 people?

00:19:52.660 --> 00:19:54.740
Well, there was a school nearby,

00:19:54.740 --> 00:19:58.619
and so they divided the full group into classrooms there.

00:19:58.619 --> 00:20:03.619
Well, I can see there is a tremendous amount of work

00:20:03.619 --> 00:20:05.420
to do in India.

00:20:05.420 --> 00:20:08.339
And we have a lovely video to show it to you.

